Hello everyone!😃

The Linux Kernel Mentorship Program 🖥️ offers a structured remote learning opportunity to aspiring Linux Kernel developers. Experienced Linux Kernel developers and maintainers mentor volunteer mentees and help them become contributors to the Linux Kernel.🤝🏻

The Linux Kernel Mentorship program - open for all undergraduates: Its a 12 week paid mentorship under which students work with mentors on certain projects. Please check the Fall 2020 Linux Kernel Mentorship Program and get started. This is a remote opportunity and there is no need to relocate or move to participate.

🔹For further process and information, visit the links mentioned below:
 1. https://wiki.linuxfoundation.org/lkmp
 2. https://people.communitybridge.org/

▪️P.S: We strongly encourage applicants who are from traditionally underrepresented or marginalized groups in the technology and open source communities, including, but not limited to: persons identifying as LGBTQ, women, persons of color, and/or persons with disabilities.

Thank you
Regards,
